class AddActualLocations < ActiveRecord::Migration
  def up
    {
      "Abecean Longfin" => "Abecean Longfin is a silvery fish that can be caught in lakes, ponds and rivers. A good way to find them is to look for dragonflies above the water: you can usually find a Longfin or two right beneath them. They can also be found in fish barrels or sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Bear Claws" => "Bear claws are dropped by killed bears, which can be found in the Skryim wilderness or cave lairs.",
      "Bee" => "Bees are flying insect that can be caught as they fly around. They're commonly found near beehives and can also be found in them. Several beehives can be found near Honeystrand cave, south of Ivarstead. Bees are also commmonly sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Beehive Husk" => "Beehive Husks are collected from beehives. Look out for bees flying around: a beehive might be close nearby. Several beehives can be found near Honeystrand cave, south of Ivarstead.",
      "Bleeding Crown" => "Bleeding Crown are mushrooms with red/purple caps, which are commonly found in caves. The largest source of Bleeding Crown is Chillwind Depths, a mountain cavern on the border of Hjaalmarch and The Reach.",
      "Blisterwort" => "Blisterwort are red-capped mushrooms commonly found in caves. The largest source of Blisterwort is Chillwind Depths, a mountain cavern on the border of Hjaalmarch and The Reach.",
      "Blue Butterfly Wing" => "Blue Butterfly Wings can be harvested by catching blue butterflies. Butterflies can be found during the day in non-snowy areas. A large collection of butterflies exists near Talking Stone Giant Camp, northeast of Rorikstead along the Hjaal river.",
      "Blue Dartwing" => "Blue Dartwings can be harvested by catching blue dragonflies. Dragonflies are normally found near water during the day. A large collection of dragonflies exists near The Apprentice Stone, on a island in the march west-northwest of Morthal.",
      "Blue Mountain Flower" => "Blue Mountain Flowers are, as the name suggests, blue flowers. They look the same as purple and red mountain flowers, and can be found in large droves in the foothills and below the snowline in the mountains. A large collection of Blue Mountain Flowers can be found near Sleeping Tree Camp, southeast of Rorikstead, and they are frequently sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Bone Meal" => "Bone Meal is dropped by undead, such as skeletons and draugr, both of which may drop a sample. They're always dropped by Dragon Priests and are frequently sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Briar Heart" => "Briar Hearts are dropped by Forsworn Briarhearts. Briarhearts can usually be found in Forsworn camps, such as Lost Valley Redoubt. There are also a couple of Briar Hearts in Gallows Rock.",
      "Butterfly Wing" => "Blue Butterfly Wings can be harvested by catching orange monarch butterflies. Butterflies can be found during the day in non-snowy areas. A large collection of butterflies exists near Talking Stone Giant Camp, northeast of Rorikstead along the Hjaal river.",
      "Canis Root" => "Canis Root is harvested from small gnarled bushes. They are usually found near near rock formations or the base of cliffs in the Rift, or in swampy regions in Hjaalmarch. The largest collection of Canis Roots can be found around Folgunthur, east of Solitude, or Pinepeak Cavern, north of Ivarstead.",
      "Charred Skeever Hide" => "Charred Skeever hides are collected from Skeevers roasting over a fire, commonly in bandit or giant camps. You cannot create Charred Skeever Hides yourself. See Tolvald's Cave, northeast of Shor's Stone, or Alftand, southeast of Winterhold, for of Charred Skeever Hides.",
      "Chaurus Eggs" => "Charus Eggs can be found in Falmer hives, and they are also dropped by Chaurus and Chaurus Reapers. They are round and glow with a pale blue light, making them easy to spot even in caves. Frostflow Lighthouse, west of Winterhold, has a huge number of Chaurus Eggs.",
      "Chicken's Egg" => "Chicken's Eggs can be found in chicken nests around farms. Nests are usually under a low sloping roof, but can sometimes just be found on the ground. There's a large number of Chicken's Eggs in the Thalmor Embassy in Haafingar.",
      "Creep Cluster" => "Creep Cluster are harvested from orange-colored roots growing on rocks. They're generally only found in Eastmarch, with a large collection found near Steamcrag Camp, south of Windhelm.",
      "Crimson Nirnroot" => "Crimson Nirnroot is a special type of Nirnroot found exclusively in Blackreach. Like normal Nirnroots, the crimson variant is usually found near water and makes a chiming sound when you get near it.",
      "Cyrodilic Spadetail" => "Cyrodilic Spadetail is a red fish that can be caught in lakes, ponds and rivers. They're more commonly found in shallow water: a good spot to find them is in the water around The Apprentice Stone, west-northwest of Morthal. Cyrodilic Spadetail can also be found in fish barrels or sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Daedra Heart" => "Daedra Hearts are dropped by slain Dremora. In addition to alchemical uses, they're also used to make Daedric armor and weapons. Dremora are rare in Skyrim, but can be found in the Shrine of Mehrunes Dagon, Shalidor's Maze and Azura's Star Interior. They're sometimes sold by alchemy vendors, and almost always by Enthir at the College of Winterhold.",
      "Deathbell" => "Deathbells are large blue-colored flowers. They are commonly found in swampy areas, such as Hjaalmarch, with a large number of them in the Forelhost Refectory in the Forelhost ruin southest of Riften.",
      "Dragon's Tongue" => "Dragon's Tongue is a yellow flower. They are usually found in Eastmarch, with large collections around Steamcrag Camp, Witchmist Grove and Bonestrewn Crest, all of which can be found in close to each other south of Windhelm.",
      "Dwarven Oil" => "Dwarven Oil is dropped by Dwarven Automatons, which can be found in dwarwen ruins. Dwarven centurions will always drop it, while other automatons such as spheres and spiders will drop it half of the time. Mzinchaleft, southwest of Dawnstar, is a good source of Dwarwen oil in particular.",
      "Ectoplasm" => "Ectoplasm are wooden bowls with grey-green contents. They're dropped by ghosts and other etheral undead, which can be found in various dungeons. There are also several samples of Ectoplasm in the Hall of Countenance in the College of Winterhold and in The Mortar and Pestle shop in Dawnstar.",
      "Elves Ear" => "Despite the name, Elves Ears aren't actual ears, but rather a plant normally hanging to dry inside buildings. Good places to find them are Dragonsreach in Whiterun, Castle Dour in Solitude and Thalmor Embassy in Haafingar. They are also frequently sold by vendors.",
      "Eye of Sabre Cat" => "Eyes of Sabre Cats are sometimes dropped by Sabre Cats instead of teeth. Sabre Cats can be found everywhere in the Skyrim wilderness, and occasionally samples of their eyes can be found on peddlers and Forsworn. A couple of eyes can also be found near Karthspire Camp, east of Morthal.",
      "Falmer Ear" => "Falmer Ears are the actual ears of Falmers, and can be found on their bodies. Falmers can be found in underground lairs, often near Dwarven ruins. There are also a whole bunch of ears in the Alftand ruins, southwest of Winterhold, and in Forelhost, southeast of Riften.",
      "Fire Salts" => "Fire Salts are a wooden bowl with orange contents, and are typically dropped by Flame Atronachs and Flame Thralls. Unfortunately, summoned atronachs don't drop any salts, and finding non-summoned Flame Atronachs can be tricky. Nightcaller Temple, overlooking Dawnstar, and The Mortar and Pestle shop in Dawnstar, will have samples of Fire Salts as well.",
      "Fly Amanita" => "Fly Amanita are mushrooms easily identified by their with red caps. They're commonly found in caves, with the largest source of Fly Amanita being Pinemoon Cave, northwest of Dragon Bridge, and Geirmund's Hall, east of Ivarstead.",
      "Frost Mirriam" => "Frost Mirriam are dried plants found hanging in houses, often near garlic and elves ears. A couple of good examples of Frost Mirriam sources are Black-Briar Lodge east of Riften, Vlindrel Hall in Markarth and Burguk's Longhouse in Dushnikh Yal, east of Markarth.",
      "Frost Salts" => "Frost Salts are a wooden bowl with white-blue contents, and are typically dropped by Frost Atronachs and Frost Thralls. Unfortunately, summoned atronachs don't drop any salts, and finding non-summoned Frost Atronachs can be tricky. Mistveil Keep in Riften, and the Grave Concoctions shop in Falkreath, will have samples of Frost Salts as well.",
      "Garlic" => "Garlic are normally found in houses, hanging from the ceiling in braids. The largest collections of garlic can be found in the Thalmor Embassy, north of Solitude in Haafingar, and in Boulderfall Cave, northwest of Riften. Garlic is frequently sold by vendors.",
      "Giant Lichen" => "Giant Lichen are red-brown fungus found outside in the marshes of Hjaalmarch. The surroundings of Movarth's Lair, north of Morthal, has a large collection of Giant Lichen, as do the areas around Morthal itself.",
      "Giant's Toe" => "Giant's Toes are appendages dropped by all varieities of Giants. The best place to look for Giants are their camps, which are scattered around Skyrim. Giants can also be found individually or in groups around the wilderness, sometimes herding Mammoths. Samples of Giant's Toes can be found in The White Hall in Dawnstar, or in the East Empire Company Warehouse outside of Solitude.",
      "Glow Dust" => "Glow Dust is easy to identify as wooden bowls with glowing contents. They are dropped by Wisps and Wispmothers, which are typically found in non-snowy wilderness. There are also samples of Glow Dust in the Shrine of Mehrunes Dagon, southeast of Morthal, or in Proudspire Manor in Solitude (if you've bought it).",
      "Glowing Mushroom" => "Glowing Mushroom are fungus growing on cave walls which are easy to spot because of their glow. A large collection of Glowing Mushrooms can be found in Tolvald's Cave, northwest of Shor's Stone in the Rift.",
      "Grass Pod" => "Grass Pods are whitish oval pods that can be harvested from grass plants. These plants normally grow along Skyrim's northern coasts and along the rivers around Morthal. Areas particularly dense with Grass Pods are around Ravenscar Hollow, northwest of Solitude, as well as the Wreck Of The Brinehammer, west of Dawnstar.",
      "Hagraven Claw" => "Hagraven Claws are sometimes dropped by Hagravens, unlike their feathers which always drop. Hagravens can often be found in the company of Forsworn, or inside of groves and lairs in the wilderness. Samples of Hagraven Claws can be found in Grave Concoctions in Falkreath, Hall of Countenance at the College of Winterhold or The White Hall in Dawnstar.",
      "Hagraven Feathers" => "Unlike their claws, Hagraven Feathers are always dropped by Hagravens. Hagravens can often be found in the company of Forsworn, or inside of groves and lairs in the wilderness. Samples of Hagraven Feathers can be found in Hag's End, which is accessible through Deepwood Redoubt west of Solitude, as well as Witchmist Grove, south of Windhelm.",
      "Hanging Moss" => "Hanging Moss is a green-brown plant often found hanging off rocky ledges, trees or dungeon ceilings. It can be found everywhere in Skyrim, but seems to be more frequent in The Reach. The Solitude Catacombs, Dustman's Cairn, northwest of Whiterun, and Kolskeggr Mine, east of Markarth, all have large collections of Hanging Moss.",
      "Hawk Beak" => "Hawk Beaks are dropped by slain Hawks, which can be difficult to find and even more difficult to kill. There is a large collection of Hawks near the East Empire Company Warehouse outside of Solitude, and more just northeast of Solitude. There's also an individual Hawk Beak in Alftand, southeast of Winterhold.",
      "Hawk Feathers" => "Hawk Feathers are dropped by Hawks, of which there is a large collection near the East Empire Company Warehouse outside of Solitude, and more just northeast of Solitude. There's also an individual Hawk Beak in Alftand, southeast of Winterhold, and Silver Hand members have a high chance of carrying them as well.",
      "Histcarp" => "Histcarp is a orange-colored fish that can be caught in lakes, ponds and rivers. A good spot to find them is in the water around The Apprentice Stone, west-northwest of Morthal. Histcarp can also be found in fish barrels or sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Honeycomb" => "Honeycombs can be harvested from beehives. A good way to find beehives is looking out for bees flying around, as a beehive might be nearby. Several beehives can be found near Honeystrand cave, south of Ivarstead.",
      "Human Flesh" => "As the name describes, Human Flesh is chunks of meat off a human body and looks a lot like raw beef. Unfortunately, the ingredient cannot be looted from humans, but are found in necromancer dungeons and in locations where people have performed the black sacrement ritual to summon the Dark Brotherhood. There's a large collection of Human Flesh in Castle Volkihar (Dawnguard only); otherwise, look in Alftand, southeast of Winterhold, or Tolvald's Cave, northeast of Shor's Stone.",
      "Human Heart" => "Human Hearts cannot be looted off dead humans, but are instead found where in locations where people have performed the black sacrement ritual to summon the Dark Brotherhood. Samples exist in the Aretino Residence in Windhelm, Black-Briar Manor in Riften, and Volunruud, southeast of Morthal",
      "Ice Wraith Teeth" => "Ice Wraith Teeth are icy fangs dropped by Ice Wraith. Ice Wraiths can be found in the snowy parts of Skyrim, and also live in The Midden below the College of Winterhold. There are samples of Ice Wraith Teeth in Jorrvaskr in Whiterun as well as Hall of Attainment in the College of Winterhold.",
      "Imp Stool" => "Imp Stool are round mushrooms with yellowish caps, which are commonly found in caves. The largest source of Imp Stool is Chillwind Depths, a mountain cavern on the border of Hjaalmarch and The Reach.",
      "Jazbay Grapes" => "Jazbay Grapes are blue-purple berries that can be harvested from the golden-colored Jazbay vines that grow in Eastmarch's rocky areas. A large number of Jazbay Grapes can be found near Steamcrag Camp and Witchmist Grove, both to the south of Windhelm.",
      "Juniper Berries" => "Juniper Berries are small white berries that can be harvested from a tree-like bush that grow in The Reach. The surroundings around Dushnikh Yal and Valthume, southeast of Markarth, have a large density of Juniper Berries.",
      "Large Antlers" => "Large Antlers are antlers dropped by male Deer, Elk or White Stag; females drop Small Antlers instead. Each of the animals can be found around the Skyrim wilderness, and have a 50/50 chance of dropping antlers when killed. Peddlers sometimes carry antlers as well; Vaermina Devotees in Nightcaller Temple have a very small chance of dropping them as well.",
      "Lavender" => "Lavender is a purple-colored herb that grows in large parts of Skyrim, but seem to be particularly common in Whiterun hold. Many samples exist in the city of Whiterun itself, and there are a lot Lavender around Chillwind Depths, south of Dragon Bridge, as well.",
      "Luna Moth Wing" => "Luna Moth Wings can be collected by Luna Moths, which are easy to spot thanks to their glowing wings. Unlike other butterflies, Luna Moths only come out at night, and there is a lot of them around Talking Stone Camp, northeast of Rorikstead as well as inside Bloated Man's Grotto, north of Falkreath.",
      "Moon Sugar" => "Moon Sugar are bowls with yellow-brown contents. They can be difficult to find in the wilderness, but are always sold by Khajit vendors. There are also several samples of Moon Sugar in the Riften Warehouse.",
      "Mora Tapinella" => "Mora Tapinella is a mushroom with white stem and yellow-brown caps that grow on tree stumps and fallen trees in the Skyrim forests. There is a lot of Mora Tapinella around Riverwood, as well as around Northwatch Keep, northwest of Dragon Bridge.",
      "Mudcrab Chitin" => "Mudcrab Chitin are the claws of Mudcrabs and can be salvaged from their bodies. Mudcrabs can be found along riverbanks and lakeshores, and individual samples of Mudcrab Chitin can be found in Pale Imperial Camp, west of Dawnstar, and Riverside Shack, southwest of Windhelm.",
      "Namira's Rot" => "Namira's Rot are mushrooms with brownish caps, which are commonly found on cave floors. The largest source of Namira's Rot is Chillwind Depths, a mountain cavern on the border of Hjaalmarch and The Reach.",
      "Nightshade" => "Nightshade are purple flowers that normally grow around graveyards. Samples can be collected in Solitude, the Hall of the Dead in Falkreath and in Labyrinthian, a ruin southeast of Morthal.",
      "Nirnroot" => "Nirnroot is a plant that glows in the dark and makes a chiming sound when you get near them. They're usually found near water, or at Sarethi Farm between Riften and Ivarstead, where they are being cultivated.",
      "Nordic Barnacle" => "Nordic Barnacle are found in nordic barnacle clusters, which are only found underwater. A good spot to find them is Hela's Folly, a shipwreck northeast of Dawnstar.",
      "Orange Dartwing" => "Blue Dartwings can be harvested by catching orange dragonflies. Dragonflies are normally found near water during the day. A large collection of dragonflies exists near The Apprentice Stone, on a island in the marsh west-northwest of Morthal.",
      "Pearl" => "Pearls are azure-blue triangle-shaped stones which cannot be salvaged anywhere. The only way to get Pearls is to find a sample, most of which are randomly placed in Skyrim. They can usually be found in Geirmund's Hall, east of Ivarstead, and very rarely in Apothecary's Satchels.",
      "Pine Thrush Egg" => "Pine Thrush Eggs are rust-colored eggs that can be harvested from bird nests. Both Pine Thrush Eggs and Rock Warbler Eggs come from similar-looking nests, but Pine Thrush Eggs are more common in forest areas. Around Heartwood Mill, west of Riften, there's a large collection of Pine Thrush nests.",
      "Powdered Mammoth Tusk" => "Powdered Mammoth Tusks are bowls with yellowish contents. They can only be looted, and not made from mammoth tusks. Powdered Mammoth Tusks are very rare and there are no guaranteed samples; the best bet is finding peddlers randomly in the wilderness, in Apothecary's Satchels or dropped by Forsworn.",
      "Purple Mountain Flower" => "Purple Mountain Flowers are, as the name suggests, purple flowers. They look the same as blue and red mountain flowers, and can be found in large droves in the foothills and below the snowline in the mountains. Plenty of Purple Mountain Flowers can be found around Pinewatch, west of Helgen, and they are frequently sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Red Mountain Flower" => "Red Mountain Flowers are, as the name suggests, red flowers. They look the same as blue and purple mountain flowers, and can be found in large droves in the foothills and below the snowline in the mountains. A lot of Red Mountain Flowers can be found in Shadowgreen Cavern, north-northwest of Solitude. They are also frequently sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "River Betty" => "River Betty is a purple fish that can be caught in lakes, ponds and rivers (despite the name, they're no more commonly found in rivers than any other fish). They're more commonly found in shallow water: a good spot to find them is in the water around The Apprentice Stone, west-northwest of Morthal. River Betty can also be found in fish barrels or sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Rock Warbler Egg" => "Rock Warbler Eggs are green eggs found in bird nests. Both Rock Warbler Eggs and Pine Thrush Eggs come from similar-looking nests, but Rock Warbler Eggs are more common in rocky areas. A particularly good spot for Rock Warbler Eggs are the area around Valthume, southeast of Markarth.",
      "Sabre Cat Tooth" => "Sabre Cats Teeth are sometimes dropped by Sabre Cats instead of eyes. Sabre Cats can be found everywhere in the wilderness, and occasionally samples of their teeth can be found on peddlers and Forsworn. A couple of eyes can also be found in Drelas' Cottage, which is located northwest of Dustman's Cairn and south of Morthal.",
      "Salt Pile" => "Salt Piles are wooden bowls with white contents. They are extremely common throughout Skyrim and can be found in buildings and dungeons alike. Alchemy vendors and innkeepers normally have several samples for sale. A large collection of Salt Piles can be found south of Merryfair Farm, northwest of Riften.",
      "Scaly Pholiota" => "Scaly Pholiota is a light yellow fungus that grow on tree stumps and fallen trees. They're common in The Rift forests, with the areas around Darklight Tower, southwest of Riften, and Honeystrand Cave to the south of Ivarstead, being especially good for finding Scaly Pholiota.",
      "Silverside Perch" => "Silverside Perch is a silvery fish that can be caught in lakes, ponds and rivers. They're more commonly found in shallow water: a good spot to find them is in the water around The Apprentice Stone, west-northwest of Morthal. Silverside Perch can also be found in fish barrels or sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "Skeever Tail" => "Skeever Tails are dropped by Skeevers, and can also be found in any spider web sac that contains a Skeever. Skeevers are rat-like animals that can be found in caves and dungeons, as well as in the Skyrim wilderness. Additionally, a large cache of Skeever Tails can be found in the Commander's Quarters in Fort Dunstad, south of Dawnstar, as well as the Basement of Honningbrew Meadery just outside of Whiterun.",
      "Slaughterfish Egg" => "Slaughterfish Eggs are yellow-green eggs which can only be found in underwater nests, and not on Slaughterfish themselves. There's a large collection of Slaughterfish Egg nests around the Wreck Of The Brinehammer, west of Dawnstar, as well as The Serpent Stone, east of Winterhold. There's also a bunch of samples lying around in the Arch-Mage's Quarters in the College of Winterhold.",
      "Slaughterfish Scales" => "Slaughterfish Scales are the silvery scales of the dreaded Slaughterfish, and can be looted from their bodies. Slaughterfish can be found in most types of water, but especially in lakes. Collecitons of scale samples can be found in Tolvald's Cave, northeast of Shor's Stone, or Glenmoril Coven, west of Falkreath.",
      "Small Antlers" => "Small Antlers are antlers dropped by female Elk, while males drop Large Antlers instead. Elks can be found around the Skyrim wilderness, and have a 50/50 chance of dropping antlers when killed. Peddlers sometimes carry antlers as well, and a couple of samples of Small Antlers can be found in Rimerock Burrow, northwest of Dragon Bridge.",
      "Small Pearl" => "Small Pearls are azure-blue round stones which cannot be salvaged anywhere. The only way to get Small Pearls is to find a sample, most of which are randomly placed around Skyrim. They can usually be found in Geirmund's Hall, east of Ivarstead, as well as Alftand, southeast of Winterhold. Occassionally, Small Pearls are carried by Peddlers or are very rarely in Apothecary's Satchels.",
      "Snowberries" => "Snowberries are red berries that grow on the Snowberry bush. Snowberries can be found outdoors in the snowy areas of Skyrim, and are particularly prevalent in the surroundings of Bloodlet Throne, southwest of Helgen, Windward Ruins, southwest of Dawnstar and Driftshade Refuge, southeast of Dawnstar.",
      "Spider Egg" => "Spider Eggs are yellow-green eggs that can be harvested from egg and web sacs of Frostbite Spiders. Spiders are generally found in dungeons, where eggs are more likely to appear, but can also spawn in the wilderness. There's a lot of Spider Eggs in Harmugstahl, northeast of Markarth, and in Ironbind Barrow, inbetween Winterhold and Whiterun.",
      "Spriggan Sap" => "Spriggan Sap is a green-blue substance in a small ceramic bowl. It can unfortunately not be harvested from Spriggans, which drop Taproots instead. Multiple samples of Spriggan Sap can be found in Proudspire Manor in Solitude, Honeyside in Riften, and the Hall of Countenance in the College of Winterhold.",
      "Swamp Fungal Pod" => "Swamp Fungal Pods are white globe-shaped fungus growing in the marshes of Hjaalmarch. Areas with large collections of Swamp Fungal Pods are Movarth's Lair, north of Morthal, and The Apprentice Stone, northwest of Morthal, as well as around Morthal itself.",
      "Taproot" => "Taproot looks like a gnarled branch with a faint green glow. It is dropped by Spriggans, which can be found outdoors in the wilderness, as well as inside caves. Samples of Taproot can be found in Proudspire Manor in Solitude, Honeyside in Riften, as well as Nightcaller Temple in Dawnstar.",
      "Thistle Branch" => "Thistle Branch is harvested from Thistle plants, which are spiky-looking plants with purple flowers. Thistle plants are especially common in the southern pine forests, but can be found everywhere in low elevations. Large collections of Thistle Branches can be found around Riverwood, Falkreath and Pinewatch, northeast of Falkreath.",
      "Torchbug Thorax" => "Torchbug Thorax can be harvested by catching torchbugs. Torchbug can be found at night in non-snowy areas: their illuminated bodies make them easy to spot. A large collection of torchbugs exists near Talking Stone Giant Camp, northeast of Rorikstead along the Hjaal river.",
      "Troll Fat" => "Troll Fat are wooden bowls with white contents. They are dropped by trolls, which can be found everywhere in the Skyrim wilderness. Another fantastic source of Troll Fat is the East Empire Company Warehouse on the Solitude docks.",
      "Tundra Cotton" => "Tundra Cotton is a very common plant which has large white flowers that almost look like cotton balls (hence the name). The plant is very common in Whiterun Hold, with lots of samples available near Broken Fang Cave, west of Whiterun and Whitewatch Tower, northeast of Whiterun.",
      "Vampire Dust" => "Vampire Dust is a dark grey substance inside a wooden bowl. They're always dropped by Vampires, which can be found in dark lairs and caves all around Skyrim, and sometimes in the wilderness as well. Nightcaller Temple outside of Dawnstar has a few samples of Vampire Dust, as do both The Mortar and Pestle shop inside of Dawnstar itself and Honeyside in Riften.",
      "Void Salts" => "Void Salts are a wooden bowl with dark grey contents, and are typically dropped by Storm Atronachs and Storm Thralls. Unfortunately, summoned atronachs don't drop any salts, and finding non-summoned Storm Atronachs can be tricky. The Blue Palace in Solitude, Angeline's Aromatics shop in Solitude, and Proudspire Manor in Solitude (if you've bought it) will have samples of Void Salts as well.",
      "Wheat" => "Wheat are identified as large yellow bales. They're very common on farms, with large collections outside of Cowflop Farmhouse in Rorikstead and Hollyfrost Farm, east of Windhelm. They're also frequently sold by alchemy vendors.",
      "White Cap" => "White Cap are mushrooms with, as the name indicates, white caps. They're commonly found in caves. The largest source of Bleeding Crown is Chillwind Depths, a mountain cavern on the border of Hjaalmarch and The Reach.",
      "Wisp Wrappings" => "Wisp Wrappings look like long thin white film. They are dropped by Wispmothers, which are typically found in non-snowy wilderness. Peddlers randomly walking around in the wilderness also have a chance of carrying them."
    }.each do |name, location|
      Ingredient.find_by_name(name).update_attributes(location: location)
    end
  end

  def down
    Ingredient.update_all(location: nil)
  end
end
